A completely honest review after trying takeout from grill on less over 5 separate occasions and trying out 10 different dishes.  I would give them a 3/5. They are decent but definitely don’t expect anything above that, and the chicken and meats that they use often taste of low quality.  Crispy Beef (Chinese Menu) stay away! The beef is disgusting and covered in an equally terrible sauce - 1/5.  Vegetable Soup - their soup is not bad at all. Certainly not gourmet but it taste nice and hits the spot. - 5/5.  Pastrami Burger - one of their better items on the menu. The burger is flavored well, though cooked a little too much to the point of being on the dry side. Still pretty decent. - 4/5.  Chicken Soup with Matzah Ball and Noodles - again another great soup. - 5/5.  Pastrami Baguette Sandwich - not very good at all. Pastrami used here was full of fat and not much meat on it. Bread was old and stale and tasteless. - 2/5.  Cajun Fries - I mean they’re fries. Cannot go too wrong with them, and it was dried out but that it to be expected with takeout. 4/5.  Potato Knish - not bad at all. 4/5.  Chilly Burger - its very spicy! If you like heat it is not a bad burger. Similar to the other burger above it was on the dry side :( - 4/5.  Chip Fries - these are very good! Much better than the frozen variety Fries, these are fresh and taste good. - 5/5.  Sweet n Sour Chicken (Chinese Menu) - better than the beef on Chinese menu, but still pretty low quality chicken and did not taste fresh. Stick to burgers at this place I would say. - 3/5.  French Fries - boring and tasteless. - 1/5.  Grilled Chicken - not too bad, moist and had flavor to it. Not best quality. - 4/5.  Beef Egg Roll - not a lot of flavor dimension and taste like a glob of oil. - 2/5.  Sesame Chicken with Fried Rice - rice was not fried, Chicken was not good quality and sauce was missing the good flavor. Would not get again. - 3/5.
